    org.mozilla.geckoview.PanZoomController.onTouchEventForResult(MotionEvent)
    org.mozilla.geckoview.GeckoView.onTouchEventForResult(MotionEvent)
    Use GeckoView.onTouchEventForDetailResult(MotionEvent) instead. Dispatches a MotionEvent to the PanZoomController. This is the same as GeckoView.onTouchEvent(MotionEvent), but instead returns a PanZoomController.InputResult indicating how the event was handled. NOTE: It is highly recommended to only call this with ACTION_DOWN or in otherwise limited capacity. Returning a GeckoResult for every touch event will generate a lot of allocations and unnecessary GC pressure.
    org.mozilla.geckoview.GeckoSession.setMediaDelegate(GeckoSession.MediaDelegate)
    This API has been replaced by the MediaSession API and will be removed in GeckoView 91.
